rComments: I think I would have probably gotten the same mark had I not gone to one single class. I chose the class because I was excited to learn about 'other worlds' but the stories that we discussed were bizarre and hard to analyze and understand. The class itself wasn't interesting but Prof. Baker herself was one of the nicest people I ever met

I genuinely enjoyed going to Dr. Baker's class. Readings were assigned and discussed. With a hybrid model, she worked hard to make everything accessible for everyone and was always open to contrasting opinions, as well as offered really good insight on the stories. All stories were interesting and it was one of my favourite classes content-wise.

Prof Baker is the sweetest, I have no passion for CanLit, but she made it easy to digest. She takes a while to grade things but gives good feedback. Plus she is super good with extensions. Totally recommend.

Mistakes are penalized heavily, but they're easy to fix, and her criteria is mostly clear. After the first assignment, you'll know what to do. She's kind, and cares about her students ("You're more than numbers to me"). She tries to encourage debate, and enjoys contrarian viewpoints. Only 3 assignments, but they're easy. Class is workshop style.
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', 'Graded by few things', 'Gives good feedback']

rComments: Im really happy I took ENG100 with Dr. Baker, she actually cared about her students and understood the difficulties students face during a pandemic. She and her TA provided really good feedback. Always do the bonus writing assignments they really help boost you up, and seek help when you need to, she will really help you succeed!

Took this as an elective, class is easy and you're pretty much guaranteed at least a B+ if you do the work, but you really gotta impress her if you wanna get higher than a 95. She's accomidating with online school and lectures are fun, but all her assignments are pretty much due all at once so you won't know how she grades until late in the sem
Shes a really good professor, shes one of the first instructors who could really see my errors in my writing a help me improve (even though English is not my mother language)

I really like Doctor Baker. I take her online ENG1000 Intro to Essay Writing and she explains things quite well with detailed PowerPoints and detailed zoom lectures. I like how she explains her expectations clearly. She does give lots of work, but we always take up assignments in our discussion groups and we always shown where we can improve.
teacherRatingTags: ['Lots of homework', 'Gives good feedback', 'Clear grading criteria']

rComments: She really get into her lectures and tries her best to get you to get into it as well. Although, there are many assignments (essays) handed out throughout the year, with easy 5% midterms that count as unit tests in high school. Overall, good teacher, an okay grader.

She isn't bad at what she teaches, but she is honestly REALLY political - it seems like she mentions various current issues a lot and integrates her perspectives on political ideology/feminism into the lecture as examples. I don't disagree it's just like...I came here for English, please stop mentioning politics
didnt grade anything all semester, n class was a waste of tike

I HATED this class! More of a philosophy/feminist theory class than an english class! Gives WAY too much background info and doesn't actually spend time dissecting the (tough!) critical theory she assigns. On the other hand, super easy marker and assignments are simple enough. She's really nice, I just didn't like this particular course.

She is a very good teacher, you can really see her passion in the way she teaches. She also has a great sense of humor and is always available to answer questions with everyone. Her lectures were always interesting and creative. The only homework in this class was the readings and weekly quizzes.
teacherRatingTags: ['Beware of pop quizzes', 'Amazing lectures ', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Took her Women and Literature class and LOVED IT. The texts she chose for the course are really interesting because they touch on all aspects of being a woman - lots to read but worth it. She is very engaging despite the large class size, and is pretty thorough with her explanations. She's quirky and personable. Definitely recommend her class.

Baker is extremely down-to earth, professional and charming. Her lectures and slides are what you need to study to pass. She ties history, psychology, sociology and cultural references to make reading and understanding a novel multidimensional and interesting. Expect a debate and plenty of group discussions. material can be found in library or onli

Looked forward to lectures as they are more like a huge discussion and very interesting. Short stories were good picks and not too long but you must read before the class or else don't bother going. Papers and final were fair. She has a really quirky personality and always willing to help  clarify when needed. Love her, definitely recommend!

My favourite prof yet!  You can tell how passionate she is about the subject, and she's incredible at relating to students.  She always delivered interesting lectures, thoughtful lit choices, and interesting essays.  Tough grader, but fair and gave everyone in-depth feedback. Everyone loved her!  She made me appreciate and love English.

You can tell this prof is new to teaching, but she's pretty good at it! The books she chose were pretty great compared to other courses, and her lectures are easy to follow & clear. She's a really approachable person and her assignments aren't too tough. You can tell that she really loves what she's talking about.
